Date: Tue, 30 May 2023 15:44:07 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] include: Add support for prebuilt packages

    If the package Makefile contains the line
    PKG_TARGETS:=ipkg-prebuilt
    openwrt will try to use a prebuilt ipkg found in the
    prebuilt/$(BOARD) or prebuilt/$(SUBTARGET) if SUBTARGET is defined;
    if this doesn't exist it will fall back to compiling the ipkg
    unless PKG_FORCE_PREBUILT is set

Change-Id: I6b0033e721b79385241b36e5aa8f49b35d219484
Signed-off-by: Atchaya R <quic_ratchaya@quicinc.com>
---
 include/package-ipkg-prebuilt.mk | 69 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 include/package.mk               |  3 +-
 rules.mk                         |  1 +
 3 files changed, 72 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100755 include/package-ipkg-prebuilt.mk

diff --git a/include/package-ipkg-prebuilt.mk b/include/package-ipkg-prebuilt.mk
new file mode 100755
index 000000000000..8954c5c97a17
--- /dev/null
+++ b/include/package-ipkg-prebuilt.mk
@@ -0,0 +1,69 @@
+#
+# Based on include/package-ipkg.mk
+#
+# Copyright (c) 2013 The Linux Foundation. All rights reserved.
+# Copyright (C) 2006,2007 OpenWrt.org
